<span id="freeTextContainer11570905441939710739">4.5 &quot;Midwestern prairie gothic&quot; stars!!!<br/><br/><b> 2016 Honorable Mention Read </b><br/><br/> I was immensely impressed by this sophomore novel by Mr. Maltman.<br/><br/>There are so many interweaving themes and all of them dark. This takes place in southern Minnesota in the prairies where all four seasons are strong and powerful. Farmers, preachers, coyotes, wolves, murder, myths, torture, dreams and a light sprinkling of the supernatural all are present in this atmospheric, nebulous and intriguing literary novel.<br/><br/>I am purposely </span>
  <span id="freeText11570905441939710739" style="display:none">4.5 "Midwestern prairie gothic" stars!!!<br /><br /><b> 2016 Honorable Mention Read </b><br /><br /> I was immensely impressed by this sophomore novel by Mr. Maltman.<br /><br />There are so many interweaving themes and all of them dark. This takes place in southern Minnesota in the prairies where all four seasons are strong and powerful. Farmers, preachers, coyotes, wolves, murder, myths, torture, dreams and a light sprinkling of the supernatural all are present in this atmospheric, nebulous and intriguing literary novel.<br /><br />I am purposely going to keep this review short as I do not want to give anything away.<br /><br />I highly recommend this as a Halloween read that is dark, literary and will infiltrate your slumber not with nightmares but with disturbing dreams coming from the darkest reaches of your unconscious.<br /><br />Don't forget to say your prayers and keep your spouse or lover close ;)</span>
